title: Connect to GovWifi using a Windows device - GovWifi
description: Follow these instructions to connect your Windows device to GovWifi
---

<div class="govuk-width-container">
  <div class="govuk-main-wrapper">
    <div class="govuk-grid-row">
      <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-third">
        <%= partial '/shared/product/_sidebar' %>
      </div>

      <main class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds" role="main" id="main">
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Connect to GovWifi using a Windows device</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body">There are different instructions for Windows 8 and 10, and <%= link_to "Windows 7", "#connect-windows-7", class: "govuk-link" %>.

        <div class="govuk-inset-text">If you do not know which version of Windows you're using, find out <%= link_to "how to identify your operating system", "https://support.microsoft.com/en-gb/help/13443/windows-which-operating-system", class: "govuk-link" %>.</div>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="connect-windows-8">Windows 8 and 10</h2>

        <p class="govuk-body">Once you have a GovWifi <%= link_to "username and password", "/connect-to-govwifi", class: "govuk-link" %>, follow the steps below.</p>
        <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select the wifi icon in the system tray at the bottom right of your screen. You'll see all the nearby wifi networks.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>GovWifi.</strong></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">
              Select <strong>Connect</strong>.
            </p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-step-1.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of WiFi panel in Windows 8/10" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <%= partial 'shared/copy/password_instructions' %>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-step-3.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of Wifi panel with credentials open on Windows 8/10" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>OK.</strong></p>
            <p class="govuk-inset-text">
              If it says <strong>"Can't connect to network"</strong>, <%= link_to "forget the network", "#support-windows-8", class: "govuk-link" %> and try
              again.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">When you see <strong>Continue connecting</strong>, select <strong>Show certificate details.</strong></p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-step-5.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of Wifi panel confirmation on Windows 8/10" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Check that the <strong>Server thumbprint</strong> matches: </p>
            <p class="govuk-body"><strong>37 CE B5 7A 3F 38 EB 7C 66 A2 4E 90 BB 11 71 D7 BC 4D 65 1A</strong></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">If it matches, select <strong>Connect</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="govuk-body">You should now be connected to GovWifi.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="support-windows-8">Support</h2>

        <p class="govuk-body">If you're having problems, contact IT support for the building you're in.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s" id="forget">Forget the network</h3>

        <p class="govuk-body">If your device says <strong>"Can't connect to network"</strong>, it may be trying to
          use an incorrect GovWifi username and password. You need to tell it to forget that GovWifi connection and try again.</p>

        <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Go to <strong>Settings, WiFi</strong> and select <strong>Manage known networks.</strong></p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-8-step-1.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of WiFi Settings on Windows 8/10" %>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>GovWifi.</strong></p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-8-step-2.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of known networks panel on Windows 8/10" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>Forget.</strong></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Try to connect again. Make sure youâ€™re entering your username and password exactly as shown in your text or email.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="connect-windows-7">Windows 7</h2>

        <p class="govuk-body">Once you have a GovWifi <%= link_to "username and password", "/connect-to-govwifi", class: "govuk-link" %>, follow the steps below.</p>

        <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Open the <strong>Control Panel</strong>, select <strong>Network and Internet</strong> and then <strong>'Network and Sharing Center'.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>Set up a new connection or network</strong>.</p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-7-step-1.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of the Control Panel's network settings on Windows 7" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>Manually connect to a wireless network</strong>.</p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-7-step-2.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of Connection Setup Wizard on Windows 7" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">For the <strong>Network name</strong>, enter <strong>GovWifi</strong> and for the <strong>Security type</strong>, select <strong>WPA2-Enterprise</strong>. The network name is case sensitive so make sure you enter capital G and capital W.</p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-7-step-3.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of manual WiFi connection panel on Windows 7" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>Next.</strong></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>Change connection settings.</strong></p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-7-step-5.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of successfull WiFi addition on Windows 7" %>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select the <strong>Security</strong> tab and select <strong>Settings</strong>.</p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-7-step-6.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of network properties dialog on Windows 7" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Tick the <strong>Connect to these servers</strong> box. In the text box below it, enter <strong>wifi.service.gov.uk</strong>.</p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-7-step-8.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of Protected EAP Properties dialog on Windows 7" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">In the <strong>Trusted Root Certification Authorities</strong> list, select <strong>DigiCert Global Root CA</strong>. If you cannot see this option, <%= link_to "follow these steps to download the root certificate", "#download-root-certificate", class: "govuk-link" %>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Tick <strong>Enable Identity Privacy</strong> and enter <strong>anonymous</strong> to prevent your device from broadcasting your GovWifi username.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>Configure.</strong></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Untick <strong>Automatically use my Windows logon name</strong>.</p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-7-step-11.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of Identity Privacy settings on Windows 7" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>OK</strong>, then <strong>OK</strong> again to go back to the <strong>GovWifi Wireless Network Properties</strong> window.</p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-7-step-13.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of network properties dialog on Windows 7" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>Advanced settings</strong>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>User authentication</strong> from the dropdown menu under <strong>Specify authentication mode</strong>, then select <strong>Save credentials</strong>.</p>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-7-step-14.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of Advanced Connection Settings panel on Windows 7" %>
          </li>

          <li>
            <%= partial 'shared/copy/password_instructions' %>
            <%= image_tag "troubleshooting/windows-7-step-15.jpg", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Screenshot of Save Credentials dialog on Windows 7" %>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>OK</strong> to close all windows.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select the wifi logo at the bottom right of your screen and select <strong>GovWifi</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="govuk-body">You should now be connected to GovWifi.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m" id="support-windows-7">Support</h2>

        <p class="govuk-body">If you're having problems, contact IT support for the building you're in.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s" id="download-root-certificate">Download the root certificate</h3>

        <p class="govuk-body">If you cannot see 'DigiCert Global Root CA' in the Trusted Root Certification Authorities list you might not have the right certificate installed on your device. </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">If you manage your own device, you can download it from the web. If you do not, ask your local IT team for help.</p>

        <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">In your web browser, navigate
              to: <%= link_to "https://www.digicert.com/digicert-root-certificates.htm", "https://www.digicert.com/digicert-root-certificates.htm", class: "govuk-link" %>
              and select Download under 'DigiCert Global Root CA'. Save the file to the C: drive</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">To install the certificate from the Command Prompt, go to your start menu, select 'Accessories' and right click on 'Command Prompt'. Choose 'Run as administrator'.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Copy the text below:<br/>
              <code>certutil -addstore -enterprise -f "Root" c:\DigiCertGlobalRootCA.crt</code>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Right click in the Command Prompt window and select 'Paste'. Press return.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Follow the same steps for 'GeoTrust RSA CA 2018'. You can download it
              from <%= link_to "https://www.digicert.com/digicert-root-certificates.htm#intermediates", "https://www.digicert.com/digicert-root-certificates.htm#intermediates" %></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Try connecting to GovWifi again. You should now be able to select the right certificate.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>

      </main>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
